Learn. Inspire. Our History How we got to be the zoo we are today was a long and winding journey. The Zoo is home to more than 350 animals, representing over 100 different species. Read More Our Mission The Central Florida Zoo & Botanical Gardens' mission is to create connections that inspire people to take action for wildlife. Read More Central Florida Zoological Society The non-profit, 501(c)3, education and conservation organization, under the leadership of a 21-member, volunteer board, operates the Central Florida Zoo & Botanical Gardens in Sanford, FL. Read More Orianne Center for Indigo Conservation The Central Florida Zoo's cutting edge conservation facility, built specifically for the propagation of the Eastern Indigo Snake, located in Lake County, FL.
